04/03/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Government efforts to eliminate corruption and fight organised crime are earning high marks, according to a new poll by the Macedonian Institute for Democracy, Solidarity and Civil Society, reported in Monday's (3 March) edition of the <I> Utrinski Vesnik </I>.
However, the poll also found that respondents remain largely dissatisfied with attempts to improve the economic situation and the business climate in the country.
The poll was conducted by phone late last week.
(Utrinski Vesnik - 04/03/03)
